# Mania Survival - AI Coding Instructions

This is a Unity 6 mobile-first top-down arcade survival game.

## Game identity
Mania Survival is a standalone game.
Do not reference or reuse Camping With Monsters systems unless specifically requested.

## Inspiration
Inspired by the gameplay feel of Warcraft III custom games like “The Predator”:
- One powerful Monster hunts multiple Survivors.
- Survivors do not complete tasks, generators, repairs, or objectives.
- Survivors win by staying alive until the timer ends.
- Monster wins by eliminating all Survivors.
- The fun comes from panic, jukes, traps, pickups, portals, hazards, and near-death escapes.

Do not copy Warcraft III assets, names, lore, UI, sounds, icons, or copyrighted material.

## Target feel
WC3 chaos arena + tag survival + random map events + mobile arcade controls.

Player reaction goal:
“Bro, I barely escaped. Queue again.”

## Core gameplay
- 3–5 minute rounds.
- One joystick.
- 2–3 ability buttons.
- Big readable effects.
- Simple top-down readability.
- No complex inventory.
- Pickups are automatic or one-button use.

## Development rules
- Create small beginner-friendly scripts.
- One feature per prompt.
- Do not create huge manager scripts.
- Do not rewrite unrelated systems.
- Do not rename classes unless asked.
- Use public Inspector fields with [Header].
- Always explain:
  - where to attach the script
  - which Inspector fields to assign
  - how to test it in Unity

## Avoid for now
- multiplayer networking
- monetization
- gacha
- pay-to-win
- base building
- wood economy
- turrets
- campfires
- wall repair
- task objectives
- Dead by Daylight repair loop
- Among Us tasks